Project: MacSplorer — a public, MIT-licensed open-source macOS file manager
(github.com/markry/macsplorer). It stores NO user data; it operates on files but
records none in the repo.

ALLOWED (not PII in this repo):
- The project's own author & contact email: mark@ryland.net (appears in LICENSE,
  README, Info.plist, and git authorship). ALLOW it everywhere.
- "Mark Ryland" as the copyright holder / author name — he is the public author
  of this OSS project. ALLOW.
- The Apple Developer ID Team ID Q5A8FF5XXR — public by design (embedded in every
  notarized release binary and its Gatekeeper check). ALLOW.
- Generic macOS path examples in comments (~/OneDrive, ~/Library/CloudStorage/
  OneDrive-Personal, /Volumes/Foo, /Volumes/Macintosh HD). ALLOW.
- Placeholder AWS resources: my-bucket-one / my-bucket-two, arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket-*,
  all-zero account ids (000000000000), example.com / example.org. ALLOW.

WATCH ESPECIALLY (this repo is gaining an Amazon S3 provider):
- a REAL AWS account id (12 digits) or an ARN containing one
- a REAL S3 bucket name (looks like an actual private bucket, not a placeholder)
- a REAL AWS / SSO named profile that identifies a real org or person
- any real person's name other than Mark-as-author, or any third-party email
- a real personal file path or username (e.g. /Users/<a real name>/...)
- any access key, secret, token, or presigned URL
